# Postmortem: search outage
## Summary
ES node OOM-killed; search degraded 25min for 60% users.
## Timeline (UTC+8)
- 14:30 node evicted - 14:40 diagnosed - 14:55 node back
## Impact
60% of users, 25 min, no data loss.
## Root cause (5-Why)
1. node OOM-killed → 2. memory limit 4Gi < index 5Gi → 3. limit never adjusted as index
grew → 4. no alert on index-size growth → 5. no periodic capacity review in our ops SOP.
Deepest why: the ops process has no capacity-review step — a PROCESS gap, not just a config value.
## Resolution
Raised limit to 8Gi AND added the missing process control.
## Lessons learned
Config fixes don't prevent recurrence without a process control.
## Action items
- @sre add Prometheus alert on index-size growth, due 2026-06-05
- @sre-lead add weekly capacity review to ops runbook, due 2026-06-15
